"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901027","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>It is not possible to determine from information held centrally by the Ministry of Justice, the number of offenders who identify as transgender that have been convicted of offences against women, without incurring a disproportionate cost.</p>",,"Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901027/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-23T15:48:56.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901027/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901027/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-09","Hate Crime: Females","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many people identifying as trans have been convicted of offences against women in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Baroness Barker",,"Baroness Barker","HL7671"
